001package react4j.dom.proptypes.html.attributeTypes;
002
003import javax.annotation.Nonnull;
004
005/**
006 * An enumerated value to define the cells that the header element relates to.
007 */
008public final class HeaderScope
009{
010  /**
011   * The header relates to all cells of the row it belongs to.
012   */
013  @Nonnull
014  public static final String row = "row";
015  /**
016   * The header relates to all cells of the column it belongs to.
017   */
018  @Nonnull
019  public static final String col = "col";
020  /**
021   * The header belongs to a rowgroup and relates to all of its cells. These cells can be
022   * placed to the right or the left of the header, depending on the value of the <code>dir</code>
023   * attribute in the <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> element.
024   */
025  @Nonnull
026  public static final String rowgroup = "rowgroup";
027  /**
028   * The header belongs to a colgroup and relates to all of its cells.
029   */
030  @Nonnull
031  public static final String colgroup = "colgroup";
032  /**
033   * The default value.
034   */
035  @Nonnull
036  public static final String auto = "auto";
037
038  private HeaderScope()
039  {
040  }
041}
